## 9. Difference Between `parseInt()` and Other Conversions

| Method Pattern | Return Target Type | Core Functional Behavior Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **`Integer.parseInt(s)`** | Primitive `int` | Directly parses a string into a raw stack integer value. |
| **`Integer.valueOf(s)`** | Wrapper `Integer` | Parses a string but returns a heap-allocated `Integer` object instance (utilizing inner caches). |
| **`Double.parseDouble(s)`** | Primitive `double` | Parses text sequences into floating-point decimal point types. |

---

## 10. Pseudocode for `parseInt()`

```text
Start
    Read incoming literal data string containing numeric tokens
    Evaluate string structure composition matching matching sign rules
    If non-digits are detected inside sequence:
        Raise NumberFormatException abort signal
    Else:
        Transform digit blocks into binary integer format values
        Assign primitive value to the designated receiver variable
    Use numeric primitive value directly inside logic operations
End

```

