## 11. Final Summary

`Integer.parseInt()` is an indispensable method in Java used to extract primitive integers out of text data strings. It is widely used when handling user input, parsing database logs, or processing plain files. However, you must always ensure that the target string contains valid numeric digits before passing it to the method to avoid unexpected runtime crashes.
